**Title**: Empirical Validation of Energy Dissipation Rates in Stochastic Damped Systems

**Description**: This study quantifies the discrepancy between theoretical energy decay and observed dissipation in the presence of Gaussian measurement noise. By applying a non-linear regression model to the `total_energy` time series for each of the 20 oscillators, we will compute the effective dissipation rate $\beta_{eff} = -d(\ln(E))/dt$. We will then perform a sensitivity analysis to correlate $\beta_{eff}$ against the provided `damping_coefficient` and `mass_kg` parameters. Utilizing the `displacement` and `velocity` fields, we will implement a Savitzky-Golay filter to smooth instantaneous energy values before regressing the dissipation constant. This approach rigorously validates the dataset’s internal physical consistency while quantifying the bias introduced by measurement noise on energy-based parameter estimation. The final output will be a mapping of noise-induced variance in dissipation estimates across the oscillator mass range.
\end{IDEA}


